definitions.definition: Having the general shape of a lance ; much longer than wide, with the widest part lower than the middle and a pointed apex .
Of a class of knapped stone points , made without a stem , shoulders , notches , or other features that aid in attachment to a shaft .

main_definition: ( botany , mycology ) Having the general shape of a lance ; much longer than wide, with the widest part lower than the middle and a pointed apex .
